<li id="cite_note-42"><b><a href="#cite_ref-42" title="">^</a></b> Among these works are "Playwright Shaun Duggan's stage drama <i>William</i>, Douglas Coupland's 1998 novel <i>Girlfriend in a Coma</i>, Andrew Collins' autobiography <i>Heaven Knows I'm Miserable Now</i>, Marc Spitz's novel <i>How Soon is Never?</i> , the pop band <i>Shakespeare's Sister</i> and the Polish filmmaker Przemyslaw Wojcieszek's short fictional film about two Polish fans of The Smiths, <i>Louder Than Bombs</i>, are all named after songs by The Smiths.</li>
